text:
e="preserve">Emeryville is a small city in Alameda County, California.
History.
The Ohlone Native Americans lived here before 1776.
Population.
The 2010 United States Census said that 10,080 people lived in Emeryville.
Schools.
Emery Unified School District teaches kids in Emeryville. Its schools, both in the same site, are Anna Yates Elementary School and Emery Secondary School.
German International School of Silicon Valley also has a campus. In 2018 this campus will close and become separate school, called the East Bay German International School.
